    "description": "An unlocated mountainous area to which Plutarch has Spartacus reposition before his forces' defeat of the Roman force commanded by Quintus and Scrophas. Its precise location is not known, but presumably lies in the vicinity of Petelia (modern Strongoli).",
    "details": "<p>The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: near Petelia?</p>",
